  "name": "Heroic Leap",
  "type": "technique",
  "img": "icons/magic/control/debuff-energy-hold-levitate-yellow.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>Using a Melee Weapon or Unarmed Strike, you can spend&nbsp;<strong>1 AP</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>1 SP</strong>&nbsp;to perform an exceptional leap and assault a creature.</p>\n<p>You gain up to your&nbsp;<strong>Speed&nbsp;</strong>in Spaces and increase your&nbsp;<strong>Jump Distance&nbsp;</strong>by 1 on the next Long or Vertical Jump you make.</p>\n<p>You leap into the air and make an&nbsp;<strong>Attack Check&nbsp;</strong>against a target in range, and the target makes a&nbsp;<strong>Physical Save</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Attack Hit:&nbsp;</strong>It takes your Weapons damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure:&nbsp;</strong>The target falls&nbsp;<strong>Prone</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>System Tip:&nbsp;</strong>You can add Weapon to use together with that Technique. Select it on <strong>Details </strong>Tab of that <strong>Techniques</strong>.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Technique Enhancements</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Brutal Leap:</strong> <strong>(1 SP)</strong> Transfer all of the Falling damage you would usually take into the target instead (see &ldquo;Falling Attacks&rdquo; on page 55 for more).&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Heroic Slam:</strong> <strong>(1 SP, 1 AP)</strong> Compare your&nbsp;<strong>Attack Check&nbsp;</strong>against the&nbsp;<strong>PD</strong>&nbsp;of all creatures within 1 Space of you (instead of a single target).</li>\n</ul>",
